                        <item>
                <title>Re: Allies always lose [by SanFrancisco]</title>
                <link>http://www.tripleawarclub.org/modules/newbb/viewtopic.php?post_id=15570</link>
                <description>Strategy::Allies always lose&lt;br /&gt;
Attached is a revised game with good play on both sides. I&#039;ve played over 700 games of revised and would consider myself among the top 5-10 players on the map. At high levels, both players recognize all unfavorable battles, so you end up with huge stacks and trading at the borders. It&#039;s not uncommon to have 30-40 round grinding games with over 3000 TUV and nearly no battles.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Overall, Russia is way too passive. West russia is a point of strength for russia, and russia effectively concedes it for free round 1.&lt;br /&gt;- Russia R1 buy should be 3 tanks, 3 inf. 8 infantry is too passive and concedes karelia for free R1.&lt;br /&gt;- Taking West Russia R1 as Russia is required. Assuming germany bids to ukraine, standard is 3 inf, 3 tanks, 1 art, 2 fig ukr, everything else to Wrussia. To give you a sense of how big the difference is, I pretty much know 100% that axis will win after Russia&#039;s R1 move and buy.&lt;br /&gt;- Avoid trading as Russia. For example, choose to attack 1 territory with 1 inf, 2 fig instead of 2 territories with 2 inf and 1 fig. With strength, look for opportunities to attack and stack territories.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- UK R1 is too passive. uk should land africa, karelia or archangel. Africa is generally best and is safe so long as germany has no more than 5 fig, 1 bomb. with 5 fig, 1 bomb it&#039;s about an even trade, but trading evenly is very disadvantageous for germany.&lt;br /&gt;- In general uk should buy trans, inf, tanks, art, and fighters. Their role is to threaten pressure on the germany territories. this forces the germanys to play passively.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- US R1 typical buy is 1 car, 1 trans, 6 inf or something similar. 2 carriers is too defense and slows deployment.&lt;br /&gt;- in general, US should buy transports, infantry, tanks, and a few artillery&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;-Honestly, the Axis play is really poor as well&lt;br /&gt;- Germany buys too many tanks. A good allies will place so much pressure from US or UK that germany needs the infantry defensive values. It&#039;s not uncommon to buy nothing but infantry for 5-10 rounds.&lt;br /&gt;- Japan 2 factory R1 is strictly inferior to 3 transports. Anytime I see Axis do that, I know I have an auto-win against them. It also indicates that the player hasn&#039;t thought much about the game to realize why 2 factories are strictly inferior to 3 transports R1.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;My summary review of the game is that Allies played way too passive and concedes tons of territory that it didn&#039;t need to. Especially Russia. Axis played hyper-aggressively in a very suboptimal way but got a free pass because of the allied passiveness.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Allies actually have a huge advantage in Revised. If I were to play both sides without bid, I&#039;d suspect that allies would win 85-90% of the time. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Please let me know if anyone would like some clarifications.</description>
