                <title>Re: A&amp;A Revised:   Japan [by SanFrancisco]</title>
                <link>http://www.tripleawarclub.org/modules/newbb/viewtopic.php?post_id=14510</link>
                <description>Strategy::A&amp;A Revised:   Japan&lt;br /&gt;
6 Russian infantry R1 is a mistake by Russia.&lt;br /&gt;Under most optimal j1 moves, Japan wont attack bury even with only 1 Russia infantry there. The reason is that that infantry is best used for pushing into China and start trading sinkiang. Russia provides Japan with a huge option and leaves infantry out of position which would be better used around sinkiang.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Generally, hit bury and attack pearl with 1 sub, 1 dest, 1 fig, 1 bomber. If UK also takes Borneo with all available naval, I would probably hit pearl and UK navy, sparing bury. The bury territory structure is very favorable for axis, so its no problem for Japan to take r2.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There is no player in my list of the top 20 that ever stacks bury r1. I honestly don&#039;t mean to be arrogant, but anyone who does is a strong indication that they don&#039;t understand high level Axis and Allies mechanics.</description>
