                <title>Re: A&amp;A Revised:  United Kingdom [by Deltium]</title>
                <link>http://www.tripleawarclub.org/modules/newbb/viewtopic.php?post_id=13135</link>
                <description>Strategy::A&amp;A Revised:  United Kingdom&lt;br /&gt;
....and, probably one of the most critical Round 1 decisions for the UK.  Presuming that Germany sends the full Baltic fleet to Sea Zone 7, which do you prefer?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;(1) attacking with air only (2 figs + bomber), or&lt;br /&gt;(2) attacking with the Battleship + 2 transports + 2 figs + bomber.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Notably, the UK can lose this full air force very early with some bad dice (and also presuming that the Axis select subs before the transport as the OOL).   I find this attack particularly frustrating, as it seems to happen to me more than expected.   However, some players prefer this option because it doesn&#039;t require the AC build, preferring instead to swing the AC from the Indian ocean around a few turns later.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I like the naval + air attack, but there is risk here too, and as mentioned above, it does require an AC build to defend against German air.   Notably, both transports are needed in the attack, for some of the contingencies could involve losing the battleship (if only 1 transport), which is not too common, but risky enough.  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; </description>
